# description
program to interact with the udisksd daemon that manages disk drives and block devices.
It can mount, unmount, unlock, lock, loop-setup, loop-delete, power-off, smart-simulate and monitor.

# install
linux only

# To get info about a device:
udisksctl info -b <device>

# To mount a device:
udisksctl mount --block-device <device>

# To unmount a device:
udisksctl unmount --block-device <device>

# To get help:
udisksctl help
